<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,932]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,398,367,392]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[199,321,367,392]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Male:
</emphasis>
Thoracic pattern close to 
<taxonomicName box="[691,817,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beschkii">
<emphasis box="[691,817,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">H. beschkii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 32A) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado 2006:" authorityYear="1065" box="[997,1110,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis box="[997,1110,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">H. gracile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 31A), posterior lobe of prothorax reddish with central rounded black spot (Fig. 31D—posterior lobe completely reddish in 
<taxonomicName box="[1307,1436,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beschkii">
<emphasis box="[1307,1436,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">H. beschkii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 32C) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado 2006:" authorityYear="1065" box="[320,432,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis box="[320,432,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">H. gracile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 31C)). Cercus in lateral view: dorsobasal expansion present. Ventro-basal expansion small but present, occupying a little more than 1/3 length. slightly curved downward (Fig. 18B). Cercus in mediodorsal view: medial portion almost 1/2 length and longer than apical portion, apical portion longer than basal portion. Ventral expansion with long hairs covering ventral 1/2. Medial process very wide plate, apex strongly bifurcate, forming two smaller triangles, basal triangle wider than distal one and armed along anterior margin with sclerotized ridge, anterior margin of posterior triangular lobe with anterodorsally directed denticulate ridge (Fig. 18A). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[223,310,656,680]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Female</emphasis>
: Thoracic pattern (
<figureCitation box="[526,684,655,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 43" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1941,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1410,182,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-59@54.[164,1428,171,1929]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 43. Female: Heteragrion brianmayi (A) thorax in lateral view, (B) thorax in dorsal view, (C) prothorax in dorsal view; Heteragrion luizfelipei (paratype) (D) prothorax in dorsal view, (E) head in dorsal view, (F) thorax in lateral view, (G) thorax in dorsal view." pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 43F, 43G</figureCitation>
) close to 
<taxonomicName box="[795,945,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brianmayi">
<emphasis box="[795,945,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">H. brianmayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[960,1126,655,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 43" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1941,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1410,182,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-59@54.[164,1428,171,1929]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 43. Female: Heteragrion brianmayi (A) thorax in lateral view, (B) thorax in dorsal view, (C) prothorax in dorsal view; Heteragrion luizfelipei (paratype) (D) prothorax in dorsal view, (E) head in dorsal view, (F) thorax in lateral view, (G) thorax in dorsal view." pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 43A, 43B</figureCitation>
), differs by lack of pale Mshaped mark on thorax present in latter). Dorsum of head of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado 2006: 1062 -" authorityYear="1065" box="[834,979,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luizfelipei">
<emphasis box="[834,979,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">H. luizfelipei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mostly pale (
